fetch related advertisements only.</li>\r\n	<li>Gaming is also used as a mean to advertise but in the beginning experience did not produce positive results. Companies embedded advertisements at the time game was loading but players showed great annoyance. Advertisers are now searching for better ways. Many games are now inserting advertisements at different scenes of games without affecting player’s game experience.</li>\r\n	<li>Video-on-video or text on video at the time of loading is also applied. ScanScout and Adsense is a latest technology that scans the content of video and offer only relevant advertisements.</li>\r\n	<li>Publishers and advertisers now prefer collaborative working to earn more profit. Both Google and Yahoo have introduced their own ways of pricing at advertisements. Google’s smart pricing scheme allows setting prices dynamically while yahoo lets to set one price for each company rather than setting dynamic costs for products.</li>\r\n	<li>The trend that will be more common in near future is billboard contextual advertising. This advertising comprises using cameras with billboards and recording the expressions, time duration person spent on reading advertisements, and their responses. Advertisers can use this direct information for further functions.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b> Controversies</b>\r\n\r\nContextual advertisements called to controversies when unfair means were used to display them on sites without paying them. Third party software is installed on visitor’s computer. This software interacts with the browser and converts keywords on the websites into hyperlinks to the advertisements without paying the website. This technique is known as Third part hyperlinking. There are many such techniques used to illegally advertise on the websites without their permission.\r\n\r\nDifferent formats of Contextual advertisement not just compute users preferences but their behaviors as well. Developers and advertisers are working to enhance the ways of displaying advertisements to the relevant users. Contextual advertisement is now becoming one of the major sources of earning for websites.\r\n\r\nPhoto Credit: https://www.flickr.com/photos/proimos/','What Is Contextual Advertisement?','','publish','open','open','','what-is-contextual-advertisement','','','2015-04-24 10:14:22','2015-04-24 14:14:22','',0,'http://adomattic.com/?p=88',0,'post','',1),(89,1,'2015-03-21 15:25:04','2015-03-21 19:25:04','Contextual advertisements take place using specific keywords from the websites or from the search terms used by consumers. The websites that are targeted to some specific area contain keywords which are used by contextual advertisement scripts to produce and display relevant advertisements to the visitors. Such as website dedicated to food recopies will contain words relevant to foods hence script will fetch the advertisements of best food restaurants or newly written books on continental foods. Contextual advertisements can be displayed as ads on website with other web content or as pop-ups. Search engines display contextual advertisements by showing them in search results to the searcher.\r\n\r\n<strong>Latest trends in contextual advertisement</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>            </strong>Advanced trends, enhanced scripts and faster algorithms are used to display relevant advertisements on a webpage. Here we are mentioning some latest trends and facts about contextual advertisement.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Developers and advertisers are introducing new trends to present customized information and message to their audience. Several ways are devised to fetch more information about the consumers.</li>\r\n	<li>Showing relevant advertisements on web-pages is the core motive of contextual advertisement. Programmers are using latest technologies called Mediabot and Googlebot to fetch related advertisements only.</li>\r\n	<li>Gaming is also used as a mean to advertise but in the beginning experience did not produce positive results. Companies embedded advertisements at the time game was loading but players showed great annoyance. Advertisers are now searching for better ways. Many games are now inserting advertisements at different scenes of games without effecting player’s game experience.</li>\r\n	<li>Video-on-video or text on video at the time of loading is also applied. ScanScout and Adsense is a latest technology that scans the content of video and offer only relevant advertisements. Adribe is a technique that shows text advertisements on videos.</li>\r\n	<li>Publishers and advertisers now prefer collaborative working to earn more profit. Both Google and Yahoo have introduced their own ways of pricing at advertisements. Google’s smart pricing scheme allows setting prices dynamically while yahoo lets to set one price for each company rather than setting dynamic costs for products.</li>\r\n	<li>The trend that will be more common in near future is billboard contextual advertising. This advertising comprises using cameras with billboards and recording the expressions, time duration person spent on reading advertisements, and their responses. Advertisers can use this direct information for further functions.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong> </strong><strong>Controversies</strong>\r\n\r\nContextual advertisements called to controversies when unfair means were used to display them on sites without paying them. Third party software is installed on visitor’s computer. This software interacts with the browser and converts keywords on the websites into hyperlinks to the advertisements without paying the website. This technique is known as Third part hyperlinking. There are many such techniques used to illegally advertise on the websites without their permission.\r\n\r\nDifferent formats of Contextual advertisement not just compute users preferences but their behaviors as well. Developers and advertisers are working to enhance the ways of displaying advertisements to the relevant users. Contextual advertisement is now becoming one of the major sources of earning for websites.','What Is Contextual Advertisement?','','inherit','open','open','','88-revision-v1','','','2015-03-21 15:25:04','2015-03-21 19:25:04','',88,'http://adomattic.com/88-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(90,2,'2015-03-24 01:22:12','2015-03-24 05:22:12','Native advertisement can be a full page advertisement between pages of articles or it might be a tweet on twitter, it can be a status with images or other media on facebook or a post on advertisement forums. Native advertisements take on the similar format as of the webpage they are displayed on. It is mainly about how advertisements work with online publications to reach audience. It is the simplest form of display advertisement and contextual advertisements. Major difference between native and other form of display advertisement is that, other forms are highlighted using pop-ups or side sections on webpage while native advertisement comes in the flow of content.\r\n\r\nThe publications usually incorporating native ads enhance their quality by providing relevant information about different products in their articles and blogs. According to the study of IPG media lab there is similar percentage of sharing and reading native advertisement as there is of reading and sharing content. This is also considered one of the core reasons of its popularity.\r\n\r\nThe content published on authentic and famous websites go viral. The reason of incorporating advertisements is not just to share the content but also to cut the extra costs for advertisers which come when other formats on display advertising is used.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://tctechcrunch2011.files.wordpress.com/2012/06/native-ad-framework-1.jpg\" alt=\"native marketing\" />\r\n\r\n<i>image by techcrunch at their website {link to <a href=\"http://techcrunch.com/2012/06/30/a-framework-for-the-10b-native-advertising-market/native-ad-framework-1/\" title=\"techcrunch\" target=\"_blank\">http://techcrunch.com/2012/06/30/a-framework-for-the-10b-native-advertising-market/native-ad-framework-1/</a>} </i>\r\n\r\n<strong>Platforms supporting native advertisement</strong>\r\n\r\nThere are two main types of platforms that support native advertising, open, closed and hybrid platforms.\r\n\r\n<strong>Closed platforms</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>                        </strong>These platforms create profiles and contents and then promote the content having native advertisement according to specified confines. The instances are twitter promoted tweets, shared posts on facebook or content published on different websites.\r\n\r\n<strong>Open platforms</strong>\r\n\r\nContrasting closed platforms, open platforms promote content across number of other platform and native ads go to external platforms.\r\n\r\nMany mobile platforms have also been developed and launched for same purpose.\r\n\r\n<strong>Different Examples of native ads</strong>\r\n\r\nFew examples of native ads are listed below;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Native advertisements can appear in editorial contents and online editorials.</li>\r\n	<li>They can be included in videos.</li>\r\n	<li>It can be in the form of sponsored content for which brand pays to publisher.</li>\r\n	<li>Native advertisements can be a branded content created by brand for the publisher.</li>\r\n	<li>They can be incorporated in your social media posts, shared videos and images.</li>\r\n	<li>They might be in the form of In-feed ads pushing user to other publishing websites.</li>\r\n	<li>They also displayed as search results on different search engines such as google, yahoo and Bing.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nNative ads must be in the similar flow as content.\r\n\r\n<strong>Advantages</strong>\r\n\r\nChief benefits provided by native ads are;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Great possibility of customer’s visit to the content and surety of user’s response.</li>\r\n	<li>Consumers consider them content and view them for same number of seconds.</li>\r\n	<li>Effective to obtain branding goals.</li>\r\n	<li>The increase purchase rate 18% higher than banner ads.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe native content that is about viewer, reader and listener is one considered best. Native ads are supposed to enhance the quality of content by providing relevant ads to guide the reader.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nPhoto Credit : https://www.flickr.com/photos/r00s/','What Is Native Advertisement?','','publish','open','open','','what-is-native-advertisement','','','2015-04-24 07:00:29','2015-04-24 11:00:29','',0,'http://adomattic.com/?p=90',0,'post','',0),(91,1,'2015-03-21 15:28:21','2015-03-21 19:28:21','Native advertisement can be a full page advertisement between pages of articles or it might be a tweet on twitter, it can be a status with images or other media on facebook or a post on advertisement forums. Native advertisements take on the similar format as of the webpage they are displayed on. It is mainly about how advertisements work with online publications to reach audience. It is the simplest form of display advertisement and contextual advertisements. Major difference between native and other form of display advertisement is that, other forms are highlighted using pop-ups or side sections on webpage while native advertisement comes in the flow of content.\r\n\r\nThe publications usually incorporating native ads enhance their quality by providing relevant information about different products in their articles and blogs. According to the study of IPG media lab there is similar percentage of sharing and reading native advertisement as there is of reading and sharing content. This is also considered one of the core reasons of its popularity.\r\n\r\nThe content published on authentic and famous websites go viral. The reason of incorporating advertisements is not just to share the content but also to cut the extra costs for advertisers which come when other formats on display advertising is used.\r\n\r\n<strong>Platforms supporting native advertisement</strong>\r\n\r\nThere are two main types of platforms that support native advertising, open, closed and hybrid platforms.\r\n\r\n<strong>Closed platforms</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>                        </strong>These platforms create profiles and contents and then promote the content having native advertisement according to specified confines. The instances are twitter promoted tweets, shared posts on facebook or content published on different websites.\r\n\r\n<strong>Open platforms</strong>\r\n\r\nContrasting closed platforms, open platforms promote content across number of other platform and native ads go to external platforms.\r\n\r\nMany mobile platforms have also been developed and launched for same purpose.\r\n\r\n<strong>Different Examples of native ads</strong>\r\n\r\nFew examples of native ads are listed below;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Native advertisements can appear in editorial contents and online editorials.</li>\r\n	<li>They can be included in videos.</li>\r\n	<li>It can be in the form of sponsored content for which brand pays to publisher.</li>\r\n	<li>Native advertisements can be a branded content created by brand for the publisher.</li>\r\n	<li>They can be incorporated in your social media posts, shared videos and images.</li>\r\n	<li>They might be in the form of In-feed ads pushing user to other publishing websites.</li>\r\n	<li>They also displayed as search results on different search engines such as google, yahoo and Bing.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nNative ads must be in the similar flow as content.\r\n\r\n<strong>Advantages</strong>\r\n\r\nChief benefits provided by native ads are;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Great possibility of customer’s visit to the content and surety of user’s response.</li>\r\n	<li>Consumers consider them content and view them for same number of seconds.</li>\r\n	<li>Effective to obtain branding goals.</li>\r\n	<li>The increase purchase rate 18% higher than banner ads.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe native content that is about viewer, reader and listener is one considered best. Native ads are supposed to enhance the quality of content by providing relevant ads to guide the reader.','What Is Native Advertisement?','','inherit','open','open','','90-revision-v1','','','2015-03-21 15:28:21','2015-03-21 19:28:21','',90,'http://adomattic.com/90-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(93,1,'2015-03-21 16:07:30','2015-03-21 20:07:30','Contextual advertisements take place using specific keywords from the websites or from the search terms used by consumers. The websites that are targeted to some specific area contain keywords which are used by contextual advertisement scripts to produce and display relevant advertisements to the visitors. Such as website dedicated to food recopies will contain words relevant to foods hence script will fetch the advertisements of best food restaurants or newly written books on continental foods. Contextual advertisements can be displayed as ads on website with other web content or as pop-ups. Search engines display contextual advertisements by showing them in search results to the searcher.\r\n\r\n<b>Latest trends in contextual advertisement</b>\r\n\r\n<b>            </b>Advanced trends, enhanced scripts and faster algorithms are used to display relevant advertisements on a webpage. Here we are mentioning some latest trends and facts about contextual advertisement.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Developers and advertisers are introducing new trends to present customized information and message to their audience. Several ways are devised to fetch more information about the consumers.</li>\r\n	<li>Showing relevant advertisements on web-pages is the core motive of contextual advertisement. Programmers are using latest technologies called Mediabot and Googlebot to fetch related advertisements only.</li>\r\n	<li>Gaming is also used as a mean to advertise but in the beginning experience did not produce positive results. Companies embedded advertisements at the time game was loading but players showed great annoyance. Advertisers are now searching for better ways. Many games are now inserting advertisements at different scenes of games without effecting player’s game experience.</li>\r\n	<li>Video-on-video or text on video at the time of loading is also applied. ScanScout and Adsense is a latest technology that scans the content of video and offer only relevant advertisements. Adribe is a technique that shows text advertisements on videos.</li>\r\n	<li>Publishers and advertisers now prefer collaborative working to earn more profit. Both Google and Yahoo have introduced their own ways of pricing at advertisements. Google’s smart pricing scheme allows setting prices dynamically while yahoo lets to set one price for each company rather than setting dynamic costs for products.</li>\r\n	<li>The trend that will be more common in near future is billboard contextual advertising. This advertising comprises using cameras with billboards and recording the expressions, time duration person spent on reading advertisements, and their responses. Advertisers can use this direct information for further functions.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b> Controversies</b>\r\n\r\nContextual advertisements called to controversies when unfair means were used to display them on sites without paying them. Third party software is installed on visitor’s computer. This software interacts with the browser and converts keywords on the websites into hyperlinks to the advertisements without paying the website. This technique is known as Third part hyperlinking. There are many such techniques used to illegally advertise on the websites without their permission.\r\n\r\nDifferent formats of Contextual advertisement not just compute users preferences but their behaviors as well. Developers and advertisers are working to enhance the ways of displaying advertisements to the relevant users. Contextual advertisement is now becoming one of the major sources of earning for websites.','What Is Contextual Advertisement?','','inherit','open','open','','88-revi