bile advertising companies</strong>\r\n\r\nMultinational companies of Google and Microsoft are also taking part in this race by introducing their own ways of mobile advertisements. Google provides mobile targeting in its fast growing advertising program <strong>Google Adwords </strong>and has also provided well known mobile advertising program names<strong> Google Admob Ads,</strong> while Microsoft is also providing techniques to build powerful mobile ads with the options to target specific locations, device type, and platforms used that are iOS, Android and windows phone. Mobile phone versions of Microsoft products like Skype, Bing and MSN are used to display relevant ads. While using Skype you can see ads on its home page. Recent study has revealed that around 70% people use mobile version of apps.\r\n\r\nFew top mobile advertising companies are Google Admob Ads, Millennial Media, Apple’s iAd, Flurry, InMobi, ChartBoost, Has Offers and Amobee. You can use services of these mobile advertising companies to publish your ad. All have their own policies and bidding methods.\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"http://www.adweek.com/socialtimes/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2012/07/Screen-Shot-2012-07-18-at-9.28.24-AM.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"467\" height=\"353\" />\r\n<i>image by adweek at their website {link to <a href=\"http://www.adweek.com/\" title=\"adweek\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.adweek.com/</a>} </i>\r\n\r\n<strong>Tips </strong>\r\n\r\nHere we are presenting few mobile advertising tips you should follow to boost your mobile advertisement.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Increase your click-through rates by avoiding additional clicks and engaging customers more in sign-up newsletters and by providing eye catching mobile ads.</li>\r\n	<li>Make any game or useful mobile app that people will use so you will advertize your business as well.</li>\r\n	<li>Make your ad to be presented at the right time when they are needed. For instance if someone in your area is searching on Google (through mobile) about nearby hotels than your ad must be displayed so consumers will quickly click over your ad.</li>\r\n	<li>Optimize your ad according to time, location and device.</li>\r\n	<li>Offer robust call to action offers such as buy one get one free or buy it now and save your 40%.</li>\r\n	<li>Customize your ads to be shareable on social networking websites such as Facebook, Twitter, Orcut and LinkedIn.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nTake in consideration how mobile advertising and mobile marketing can fit in with your marketing program and how it can strengthen your association with your consumers. Once you measure all analytics and understand how you need to reach your customers on mobiles then you can start creating compelling and relevant messages but with great care.','Mobile Advertising-Stay around your customer','','publish','open','open','','mobile-advertising-stay-around-customer','','','2015-04-24 06:47:03','2015-04-24 10:47:03','',0,'http://adomattic.com/?p=174',0,'post','',0),(175,2,'2015-03-29 10:56:02','2015-03-29 14:56:02','People these days are more attached to their cell phones than to their TV sets or computers. They use it to communicate with their family, colleagues, friends and everyone else. They also use it for fetching instant news, playing games, reading E-Books and a lot more. Advertisers can use increasing use of mobiles as a golden opportunity to grow their marketing and to reach their customers on-the-go. There are different ad formats especially targeted to mobile phones advertising. Mobile ads can appear on videos, websites, and Google search or in apps.\r\n\r\nRecent researches have proved around 90% people use their mobile phones for doing things such as paying bills, placing orders, booking seats and other similar stuff.  Mobile ads can make you get connected with consumer personally. You can achieve your branding goals and business objectives of acquiring more custom