0 06:33:07','',0,'http://adomattic.com/wp-types-group/consulting-services/',0,'wp-types-group','',0),(182,1,'2015-03-30 01:52:27','2015-03-30 05:52:27','Sometimes you need an extra pair of hands so you can go faster.','Consulting Services','','inherit','open','open','','178-revision-v1','','','2015-03-30 01:52:27','2015-03-30 05:52:27','',178,'http://adomattic.com/178-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(183,1,'2015-03-31 10:44:26','2015-03-31 14:44:26','Social media  Impact on marketing has increased exponentially in last decade. We have number of social networking websites to contact with people. These social means can be utilized effectively for growing your business successfully. You can drive a big traffic towards your website by advertising yourself appropriately on these social sites. You can also grab local customers by joining more online ways that connect you to them. The major importance is of great content. The attractive, informative and strong content attract your customers. If you provide facts and figures about your company that you think can grab the attention of your customer so you can provide a graph showing your sales revenues or other success rates. .\n\nThere are five key things, that I believe each and every business owner needs to have in place to be successful online.\n\nFirst and foremost is a user friendly website. You want a website to have at least of your business named of course but also ways to make people able to know and contact you. You can give your email, phone number, any social information or any other media information via which you want people to access you.\n\nSecond one is to get a Face-book account and start a face-book fan page for your business and grow your following and customer circle there. You can post short videos introducing your business. You can also write about what is special about your company. Face-book is the largest social network application out there right now and it’s essential for you to have be present there to grow your business and of course to connect with your customers and followers. Large number of business based face-book groups and pages already exist, you can advertise yourself their so more people will see you.\n\nThird is Twitter, a great way to connect with other professionals, businessmen and also get a lot of information. It is also an efficient way to get lots of news and learn about new business strategies as well.\n\nFourth one is LinkedIn. It is a resume kind of website. Your LinkedIn profile holds information about your previous experiences, your current ongoing job or business and you can also publish your qualification data. On LinkedIn you should build connections with professionals, your consumers, vendors, sellers, former employees and your friends. LinkedIn profile must be robust and make yourself standout. Do not forget asking for recommendations, people love to see testimonials.\n\nLast but not least, have a blog. Some people don’t like to write but there are ways to get around that you can long blogs, short advertisements. You can also create video blog so if you are comfortable on camera then put a short video clip on your blog in place of writing out text post. Having blog establishes you as an expert. The more contacts you have online, the easier it will be for people to find you online, they will like to know and trust you and will love to do business with you.\n\n<img class=\" alignleft\" src=\"http://activex.com.pk/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/social-media-marketing.jpg\" alt=\"Social Media Networks\" width=\"334\" height=\"278\" />\n\nOther online means to advertise your business are Youtube,Instagram, Google+, Yelp and many others. All these ways are low cost with high results. So if you need to start with online marketing then get a website, make accounts on face-book, twitter, LinkedIn, yahoo, Youtube and start a blog and you will be on your way to marketing success.','Social Media Impact On Marketing','','inherit','open','open'