</strong>\r\n\r\nWhat are the possible merits now?\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Advertisers can collect relevant data about their visitors required for further tracking, reporting and analysis.</li>\r\n	<li>Any kid of display ad can be created and advertised such as online banners, paid search, natural search, E-mail ad or video and audio ad.</li>\r\n	<li>Allows cross platform tracking.</li>\r\n	<li>Image advertisements (banners can be run on Google\'s AdSense Network) could be merged to DART for Publishers</li>\r\n</ul>','How Google DoubleClick helps in marketing?','','publish','open','open','','google-doubleclick-helps-marketing','','','2015-04-24 05:52:03','2015-04-24 09:52:03','',0,'http://adomattic.com/?p=213',0,'post','',0),(214,2,'2015-04-03 11:42:00','2015-04-03 15:42:00','Double click is a part of Google’s advertising campaign used by agencies, companies, publishers, marketers and other advertisers. Some famous clients of Google double click are Microsoft, Coca-cola, Motorola, Visa UA, Loreal and Apple Inc. it is said to be one of the initial application services provider serving banner ads especially for ads. In 1998 the company was linked with an internet report with AOL, Vista, Yahoo and Excite and was also ranked as one of the top 10 worldwide websites.\r\n\r\nDouble click is an ad based technology served mainly to advertising agencies and media organizations. Double click enables them to allow users visit, target, traffic and report on their interactive ad campaigns. Double Click Company’s major product line is called DART (Dynamic advertising reporting and targeting) especially designed for publishers and advertisers.\r\n\r\nDART technology is designed to automate the administration process of buying ads for advertisers called DFA (Double click for advertisers) and helps in managing ad inventory for publishers called DFP (double click for publishers). The purpose is to enhance buying procedure for advertisers and to reduce unsold inventory for publishers.\r\n\r\nD