 learning and solving problems. AI is widely used in different fields. Artificial intelligence in marketing is used for the reason to achieve automation, accurate outputs, time and effort efficiency, decision making and to predict future market statistics. Currently largest companies such as Facebook, Google, Twitter and Amazon are using AI techniques to collect more data about their consumers and to stay in stronger connection with them. AI has provided revolutionary ways for companies to collect customer information, its assessment and making decisions based on those evaluations.\r\n\r\n<strong>Emergence of personal intelligent assistant</strong>\r\n\r\nPersonal intelligent assistant (also called virtual assistant) AI based software agents that can carry out different tasks based on user inputs, their locations and other criteria. Important tasks they can do are;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Check weather to guide which direction you should take</li>\r\n	<li>Displays and guides about products based on your search criteria and price range</li>\r\n	<li>Finds suitable restaurants, shows or shopping malls in town</li>\r\n	<li>Scheduling managements</li>\r\n	<li>Personal health management</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThere are also a lot more tasks it can perform. For marketers it has almost cut 60% cost of human employees as they only need to buy, run and use the software which doesn\'t ask for any salary or extra facilities of course.\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Role of AI in trust-able advertising</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>            </strong> Artificial intelligence based advertising assistant software communicate with consumers, suggest them best products, guide them about different things similarly as a sales-person does in any shop. Automatic processes work to notify customers about discounts, latest offers, and new products. Buyer’s data is more organized and secure which makes them trust AI-powered software. These apps are used to educate customers rather than making them 