l media platforms, conversion, Emails etc.\r\n\r\nIts main purpose is to quantify and study the effects each advertising impression leaves on purchase decision of user. Subsequent to analyzing and studying what influences customers more, marketers optimize media for conversions and compare the importance of different media channels for marketing, such as E-mail, affiliate marketing, social media networks, display ads and others.\r\n\r\nAnalyzing the whole conversion path across the whole marketing mix eliminates the accuracy challenge of analyzing data from isolated marketing means. Usually, attribution statistics are utilized by marketers to map future ad promotions and campaigns by evaluating which media assignments (ads) were the most cost-efficient as shown by metrics like eCPA (effective cost per action).\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://digitalmarketing-glossary.com/IMG/jpg/attribution-model5.jpg\" alt=\"digital attribution\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Models of attribution</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>            </strong>Rapid growth and popularity of digital advertisement and online marketing has concluded in large amount of user data for tracking, ROI and effectiveness of conversions. These new tendencies have affected the way marketers measure the effectiveness of marketing and advertising. The trends have also opened new door to development of new marketing metrics that are CPI (cost per impression), CPC (Cost per click), CPA (cost per acquisition/action), and click-through conversion. Besides this number of attribution modals have emerged with time since explosion of data and devices have boosted up the creation of attribution technology. Digital attribution is very important because it assists advertisers in analysing behaviors and responses of customers.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Single source attribution</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAlso known as single touch attribution, allocates all credit to single event or action for instance, last channel used to show ad, last click or initial click. Single attribution model does not justify and contribute to all elements involved in creating results. This is the reason model isn\'t considered verified and accurate especially by Google.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Fractional attribution</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThis attribution model comprise of consumer credit, U-curve models and equal weights. Here equal weight based models assign same amount of credit to all media channels and media mix, consumer credit involves studying guesswork or past experiences of customers to assign credits, and whole credit is allocated to first and final click in U-curve where idle actions are ignored across conversion path.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Algorithmic attribution</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThis model of attribution utilizes proprietary algorithms to allocate conversion among all touch points before conversions with the help of auto scripts to locate where credit is unpaid. Model is started from very first event level and assesses converting and non-converting paths crosswise all media channels. After that weights are combined to figure out hidden associations and correlations inside marketing.','Digital attribution','','inherit','open','open','','228-autosave-v1','','','2015-04-09 10:50:28','2015-04-09 14:50:28','',228,'http://adomattic.com/228-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(255,2,'2015-04-12 14:15:07','2015-04-12 18:15:07','<strong>Introduction </strong>\r\n\r\nGoogle AdWords is an advertising campaign run by Google. It allows advertisers to advertise their ads on Google or other partner websites (of Google) called Display Network. Advertisers are only charged when their ad is clicked by a user. There are number of other bidding options you take. The ad gets appeared to customers when they need something related to your business this increases the probably of their visits to your website. Google AdWords provide advanced options to make advertisement of high quality and format. You just need to go to Google AdWords official website, register an account, follow steps of making advertisement, set a suitable bidding option and advertise.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7662/17124130405_0c88c31f54_b.jpg\" alt=\"Average Cost per click by devices \" />\r\n\r\n<em>Average Cost per click by devices</em>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Optimize your ad</strong>\r\n\r\nGoogle AdWords offers different targeting methodologies for advertisers to help them optimize their ad and to target visitors of specific areas, language and at specific times.\r\n\r\nYou can choose where you want your ad to be displayed, which website, geographical location or even which region of any country. Advertisers are also facilitated with around 40 languages for campaign targeting. Other options are mobile targeting which involves displaying ads only to mobile users and time targeting in which ad is displayed only at a specified time.\r\n\r\n<strong>How it works?</strong>\r\n\r\nGoogle displays your ad when user writes search query in Google search box. According to the level of association between search query and advertiser’s given keywords ads are displayed above and at right side of search results.\r\n\r\nThe major question is how Google decides placement locations for your ads. Google is also in partnership with number of other website called <strong>display Network. </strong>\r\n\r\nDepending on;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>your biding option</li>\r\n	<li>Quality of your website and ads</li>\r\n	<li>Anticipated impact of your ads and their formats on visitors</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nGoogle decides where your ad will be displayed.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Measure marketing aspects</strong>\r\n\r\n“Half of my advertising money got wasted, but I don’t know which half.” this is an old marketing maxim which clearly represents the value of appropriate advertising area. With Google ads you can chase every marketing aspect of your business. It shows results about where areas of world you are getting more visitors from, which bidding option have been used more, clicks, impressions and acquisitions by visitors. Measurement of conversion rates and Return on investment (ROI) is super easy. You need to optimize your ad by using SEO keywords that are specific to your business.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Tips </strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>At the time of setting ad, make a list of relevant keywords. It’s better to use more specific keywords rather than general to get visitors who are actually interested in services and products you provide.</li>\r\n	<li>Bid high initially and avoid bidding wars</li>\r\n	<li>Test different versions of ad</li>\r\n	<li>Optimize you advertisement.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Save your money</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nGoogle AdWords only charges what you want to pay, no extra charges. You get full control of advertising costs. You can also set an average daily budget and select how you will spend on advertising in Google AdWords. For instance you have set $2 CPC bid for your advertisement, then $2 is the maximum amount you will have to pay for one click on your advertisement.','What is Google AdWords and how it sparks marketing?','','inherit','open','open','','169-revision-v1','','','2015-04-12 14:15:07','2015-04-12 18:15:07','',169,'http://adomattic.com/169-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(256,2,'2015-04-12 14:24:29','2015-04-12 18:24:29','<strong>Introduction </strong>\r\n\r\nGoogle AdWords is an advertising campaign run by Google. It allows advertisers to advertise their ads on Google or other partner websites (of Google) called Display Network. Advertisers are only charged when their ad is clicked by a user. There are number of other bidding options you take. The ad gets appeared to customers when they need something related to your business this increases the probably of their visits to your website. Google AdWords provide advanced options to make advertisement of h