 interactive display ads. Both marketers and app publishers need to run their own ads to promote their apps and other products. Mobile advertising is suitable for every kind of business and app to be promoted.\r\n<h2>What to know before advertising on mobile?</h2>\r\nBefore you run ad on mobile you should consider the following points;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>What are the types of mobile ads that advertisers can make use of</li>\r\n	<li>What are different mobile devices that you will be running your ad on like smartphone, blackberry, iPhones and other devices that can make calls?</li>\r\n	<li>How can user click on the ad, what are the easiest and preferred ways?</li>\r\n	<li>Understand conversion rates.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Where mobile ads can appear and their types</h2>\r\n<table style=\"height: 554px; margin: 5px;\" border=\"2\" width=\"607\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" width=\"213\"><strong>NO</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" width=\"213\"><strong>Where they become visible?</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" width=\"213\"><strong>Types of mobile ads</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" width=\"213\"><strong>                     1 </strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" width=\"213\">Your ads can appear on different mobile devices that can be iPhones, tablets, smartphones etc, with full browsers and internet connection.</td>\r\n<td width=\"213\">1)      Textual ads\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">2)      Picture ads</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">3)      Video ads</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">4)      Banners</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">5)      Google built ads such as Google adsense and AdWords</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" width=\"213\"><strong>                  2 </strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" width=\"213\">You can also see mobile ads during using apps or playing games on cell phones</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" width=\"213\">Text, image, banners, video based promotion ads</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" width=\"213\"><strong>             3</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" width=\"213\">Mobile ads are only displayed on devices that can make call that are cell phones, iPhones, iPads, tablets etc</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" width=\"213\">Call based advertisements</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n<h2>Traditional v/s contemporary mobile ads formats</h2>\r\nTraditionally mobile ads were only simplest versions of display ads such as simple online banners and user were supposed to click them. There were no advanced ways of interacting users, gathering their delicate information and analyzing their purchase behaviors. Latest techniques involve targeting customer’s geographical locations, time, languages, age, and business fields. Business are greatly benefited by mobile ads as they can reach their customers on needed time, at needed location and can provide them exactly what they need.\r\n\r\nMoving from old trends mobile ads is now more interactive. Several companies are using vibration feature to engage customer same as discovery channel promoted their show “storm chasers” on phones that produced sounds and vibration to give sound of storm. Other multinational companies such Google, MacDonald’s, and coke have also made ad campaigns on mobile phones to stay on finger tips of their consumers.\r\n\r\nPreviously the concept was that no one wants to buy on mobiles but the concept has been greatly changed during past few years. Latest statistics of Mojiva study shows, m-commerce and mobile shopping are fastest growing trends now.\r\n\r\nMarketers can create mobile ads using different platforms including Google AdWords and Adsense ad making platforms. Practices are getting enhanced and user experiences are becoming secure and friendly. Companies are trying to get more sophisticated ads for their brands and want to have more information and personal interaction with their consumers.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"433\"]<img src=\"http://farm9.staticflickr.com/8793/17134980495_b2aa8dcbba_b.jpg\" alt=\" Mobile Analytics and well known companies using them \" width=\"433\" height=\"346\" /> Mobile Analytic and well known companies using them[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Types and trends of Mobile advertising','','inherit','open','open','','263-revision-v1','','','2015-04-16 23:11:51','2015-04-17 03:11:51','',263,'http://adomattic.com/263-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(282,1,'2015-04-16 23:41:13','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<div id=\n<script type=\"text/javascript\">\n(function(){\n  document.adomattic = \'rpaEjsAvGCiuQQWH5qtjC4\';\n  var ai = document.createElement(\'script\');\n  ai.type = \"text/javascript\";\n  ai.async = true;\n  ai.src = \"scripts/all.js\";\n  var s = document.getElementsByTagName(\'script\')[0];\n  s.parentNode.insertBefore(ai, s);\n})();\n</script>\n        ','testing','','draft','open','open','','','','','2015-04-16 23:41:13','2015-04-17 03:41:13','',0,'http://adomattic.com/?page_id=282',0,'page','',0),(283,1,'2015-04-16 23:40:18','2015-04-17 03:40:18','<script type=\"text/javascript\">\r\n(function(){\r\n  document.adomattic = \'rpaEjsAvGCiuQQWH5qtjC4\';\r\n  var ai = document.createElement(\'script\');\r\n  ai.type = \"text/javascript\";\r\n  ai.async = true;\r\n  ai.src = \"scripts/all.js\";\r\n  var s = document.getElementsByTagName(\'script\')[0];\r\n  s.parentNode.insertBefore(ai, s);\r\n})();\r\n</script>\r\n        ','testing','','inherit','open','open','','282-revision-v1','','','2015-04-16 23:40:18','2015-04-17 03:40:18','',282,'http://adomattic.com/282-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(284,1,'2015-04-23 21:26:35','2015-04-24 01:26:35','<div class=\"adomattic-y\">\r\n<script type=\"text/javascript\">\r\n(function(){\r\n  \'use strict\';\r\n  document.adomattic = \'kCPTCq5J3r6owZoV8gSLua\';\r\n  var ai = document.createElement(\'script\');\r\n  ai.type = \'text/javascript\';\r\n  ai.async = true;\r\n  ai.src = \'http://app.adomattic.com/static/impressions/dist/all.js\';\r\n  var s = document.getElementsByTagName(\'script\')[0];\r\n  s.parentNode.insertBefore(ai, s);\r\n})();\r\n</script>\r\n</div>','test','','publish','open','open','','test-4','','','2015-05-07 08:55:31','2015-05-07 12:55:31','',0,'http://adomattic.com/?page_id=284',0,'page','',0),(285,1,'2015-04-17 10:12:10','2015-04-17 14:12:10','<div class=\"magneto-unit\">\r\n<script type=\"text/javascript\">\r\n(function(){\r\n  document.adomattic = \'rpaEjsAvGCiuQQWH5qtjC4\';\r\n  var ai = document.createElement(\'script\');\r\n  ai.type = \"text/javascript\";\r\n  ai.async = true;\r\n  ai.src = \"scripts/all.js\";\r\n  var s = document.getElementsByTagName(\'script\')[0];\r\n  s.parentNode.insertBefore(ai, s);\r\n})();\r\n</script>\r\n</div>','test','','inherit','open','open','','284-revision-v1','','','2015-04-17 10:12:10','2015-04-17 14:12:10','',284,'http://adomattic.com/284-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(287,2,'2015-04-17 10:16:53','2015-04-17 14:16:53','Google DoubleClick is a part of Google’s advertising campaign used by agencies, companies, publishers, marketers and other advertisers. Some famous clients of Google double click are Microsoft, Coca-cola, Motorola, Visa UA, Loreal and Apple Inc. it is said to be one of the initial application services provider serving banner ads especially for ads. In 1998 the company was linked with an internet report with AOL, Vista, Yahoo and Excite and was also ranked as one of the top 10 worldwide websites.\r\n\r\nGoogle DoubleClick is an ad based technology served mainly to advertising agencies and media organizations. Double click enables them to allow users visit, target, traffic and report on their interactive ad campaigns. Double Click Company’s major product line is called DART (Dynamic advertising reporting and targeting) especially designed for publishers and advertisers.\r\n\r\nDART technology is designed to automate the administration process of buying ads for advertisers called DFA (Double click for advertisers) and helps in managing ad inventory for publishers called DFP (double click for publishers). The purpose is to enhance buying procedure for advertisers and to reduce unsold inventory for publishers.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"413\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7601/16936639378_188fc4b1cd_b.jpg\" alt=\"Google DoubleClick\" width=\"513\" height=\"200\" /> Google Double Click[/caption]\r\n\r\nDouble click got <strong>Performics</strong> in 2004. Performics is a top performance marketing service provider that offers paid search, social display, natural search affiliate marketing, mobile advertising, search engine optimization and search engine marketing.  All these marketing performance services are taken in into DART system and rebrand DART search. Double click advertising exchange version 2007 have now even moved on by providing connection on advertising exchange in both media buyers and sellers, similarly as traditional stock exchange.\r\n<h2>Data collection via Google doubleClick</h2>\r\nTo collect user data Google DoubleClick targets many areas such as IP addresses, referrals to user information saved in cookies on their machines or business regulations set by any client. Here are some major kinds of collected information; operating system information, ISP (Internet service provider), Bandwidth data, Time of day and web browser. This data can also be used for the purpose to display customize ads to the visitors. Along with this, cookie information might be used to target ads depending on the number of times visitor has been exposed to any provided message, also called frequency capping.\r\n<h2>Cons and Pros of Google DoubleClick</h2>\r\n<strong>Cons</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Google takes its appropriate share from online advertising services from publishers and advertisers.</li>\r\n	<li>As Google possesses Gmail and has an unbelievable amount of data on its users, the whole misguided cookie/privacy dispute can reignite.</li>\r\n	<li>Microsoft and other companies failed the competition to buy DoubleClick which increases the possibility of developing strict tracking rules for cookies and can make information tracking harder.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Pros</strong>\r\n\r\nWhat are the possible merits now?\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Advertisers can collect relevant data about their visitors required for further tracking, reporting and analysis.</li>\r\n	<li>Any kid of display ad can be created and advertised such as online banners, paid search, natural search, E-mail ad or video and audio ad.</li>\r\n	<li>Allows cross platform tracking.</li>\r\n	<li>Image advertisements (banners can be run on Google\'s AdSense Network) could be merged to DART for Publishers</li>\r\n</ul>','How Google DoubleClick helps in marketing?','','inherit','open','open','','213-revision-v1','','','2015-04-17 10:16:53','2015-04-17 14:16:53','',213,'http://adomattic.com/213-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(288,2,'2015-04-17 10:19:52','2015-04-17 14:19:52','Google DoubleClick is a part of Google’s advertising campaign used by agencies, companies, publishers, marketers and other advertisers. Some famous clients of Google double click are Microsoft, Coca-cola, Motorola, Visa UA, Loreal and Apple Inc. it is said to be one of the initial application services provider serving banner ads especially for ads. In 1998 the company was linked with an internet report with AOL, Vista, Yahoo and Excite and was also ranked as one of the top 10 worldwide websites.\r\n\r\nGoogle DoubleClick is an ad based technology served mainly to advertising agencies and media organizations. Double click enables them to allow users visit, target, traffic and report on their interactive ad campaigns. Double Click Company