k</h2>\r\n<strong>Cons</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Google takes its appropriate share from online advertising services from publishers and advertisers.</li>\r\n	<li>As Google possesses Gmail and has an unbelievable amount of data on its users, the whole misguided cookie/privacy dispute can reignite.</li>\r\n	<li>Microsoft and other companies failed the competition to buy DoubleClick which increases the possibility of developing strict tracking rules for cookies and can make information tracking harder.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Pros</strong>\r\n\r\nWhat are the possible merits now?\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Advertisers can collect relevant data about their visitors required for further tracking, reporting and analysis.</li>\r\n	<li>Any kid of display ad can be created and advertised such as online banners, paid search, natural search, E-mail ad or video and audio ad.</li>\r\n	<li>Allows cross platform tracking.</li>\r\n	<li>Image advertisements (banners can be run on Google\'s AdSense Network) could be merged to DART for Publishers</li>\r\n</ul>','How Google DoubleClick helps in marketing?','','inherit','open','open','','213-revision-v1','','','2015-04-17 10:19:52','2015-04-17 14:19:52','',213,'http://adomattic.com/213-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(289,2,'2015-04-17 10:21:29','2015-04-17 14:21:29','','11','','inherit','open','open','','11','','','2015-04-17 10:21:29','2015-04-17 14:21:29','',213,'http://adomattic.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/11.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(292,2,'2015-04-22 16:19:27','2015-04-22 20:19:27','<strong>What is data modeling?</strong>\r\n\r\nData modeling is the process of modeling information system and data with the help of some modeling techniques. These modeling techniques specify what entities exist in database and how they are connected with one another. Data modeling is the essential part of data warehouses because it highlights the analytical requirements of decision makers.\r\n\r\nData is the heart of any company and it needs to be clear and organized. Company must know how data is related with other information, how everything is supposed to go on. For example, if company has hired 300 workers and is currently dealing with 1000 customers plus also keeping data of all products, services, and schedules. Then the company must have a strong database and a data warehouse. But to elaborate the inner structure a clear model must be made so stakeholders will have a clear notion of data.\r\n\r\nProcess involves close collaboration of expert data modelers with company stakeholders.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Types of data modeling</strong>\r\n\r\nMainly there are three data models in the way from requirement analysis to a complete functional database.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Conceptual data model</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAlso called semantic data model. The model deals with tool independent data model framed to show big picture of future information system and final data model. Model can have attributes with entities, some relationships and components of data but it will not cover deep details but just for conveying major thought. The model is then presented to owners of company; idea is made clear then if model is approved professionals sign an agreement for further work.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Logical data model</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nOnce conceptual data model is approved, professional translate it into logical data model. This model draws a comprehensible structure of database. Keep in mind, one conceptual data model can have multiple logical data models. The LDM contains complete database structure that has all attributes, entities, all possible connections and relationships. Model is fully normalized but sometimes due to factors like change of time de-normalization can occur.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Physical data model</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nFinal stage is the conversion of logical data mode into physical data model. Data is arranged into tables within a database. All constraints are applied. Attributes and entities are linked and database is normalized.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Modeling methodologies</strong>\r\n\r\nData models stand for information systems whilst there are several ways to craft data models, major are two, top-down and bottom-up:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Bottom-up data models are end results of remaking of existing stuff. Professionals study existing data forms, fields, reports and screens to make models. Bottom-up based models are mostly application-specific and physical but don’t support sharing especially if designed without reference to other components of company.</li>\r\n	<li>Top-down models start from a big picture and are created in conceptual way by collecting information from those who have knowledge about work area. The model might not cover up all entities and attributes can be used as a template.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Advantages of data modeling</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>To provide enough details about data to technical teams for building physical database.</li>\r\n	<li>Data modeling plays it role in communicating business roles and processes within and outside of the business.</li>\r\n	<li>Defines importance of businesses</li>\r\n	<li>Major advantage is that it makes sure a clean and comprehensible representation of all data objects highlighted by functional groups.</li>\r\n</ul><img src=\"http://www.ariscommunity.com/system/files/editor/image/evkl/Phases%20of%20database%20design.png\" alt=\"phase of Data modeling\" />\r\n\r\n<i>image by Aris community at their website {link to <a href=\"http://www.ariscommunity.com/\" title=\"Arisd community\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.ariscommunity.com/</a>} </i>','Data modeling','','publish','open','open','','data-modeling','','','2015-04-24 03:43:38','2015-04-24 07:43:38','',0,'http://adomattic.com/?p=292',0,'post','',0),(293,2,'2015-04-20 11:07:48','2015-04-20 15:07:48','<strong>What is data modeling?</strong>\r\n\r\nData modeling is