e LDM contains complete database structure that has all attributes, entities, all possible connections and relationships. Model is fully normalized but sometimes due to factors like change of time de-normalization can occur.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Physical data model</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nFinal stage is the conversion of logical data mode into physical data model. Data is arranged into tables within a database. All constraints are applied. Attributes and entities are linked and database is normalized.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Modeling methodologies</strong>\r\n\r\nData models stand for information systems whilst there are several ways to craft data models, major are two, top-down and bottom-up:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Bottom-up data models are end results of remaking of existing stuff. Professionals study existing data forms, fields, reports and screens to make models. Bottom-up based models are mostly application-specific and physical but don’t support sharing especially if designed without reference to other components of company.</li>\r\n	<li>Top-down models start from a big picture and are created in conceptual way by collecting information from those who have knowledge about work area. The model might not cover up all entities and attributes can be used as a template.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Advantages of data modeling</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>To provide enough details about data to technical teams for building physical database.</li>\r\n	<li>Data modeling plays it role in communicating business roles and processes within and outside of the business.</li>\r\n	<li>Defines importance of businesses</li>\r\n	<li>Major advantage is that it makes sure a clean and comprehensible representation of all data objects highlighted by functional groups.</li>\r\n</ul>','Data modeling','','inherit','open','open','','292-revision-v1','','','2015-04-20 11:11:32','2015-04-20 15:11:32','',292,'http://adomattic.com/292-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(295,2,'2015-04-27 14:30:16','2015-04-27 18:30:16','Today’s customer is a cross platform user with having number of social media user accounts. Marketers who only put their focus on marketing over particular social media platforms are likely to neglect thousands or even millions of their customers. In contemporary age of online world, advertisers and publishers are benefited with a lot many ways such as Facebook, Twitter, YouTube, platforms, search engine results and emails for reaching consumers. In this editorial we are going to converse about how assimilating your marketing processes on social media platforms and on email can be valuable to your business. Above and beyond this you will also come to know about some of the easy ways of mixing both marketing strategies.\r\n\r\n<img class=\" aligncenter\" src=\"http://websuccessteam.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/email-vs-socialmedia1.jpg\" alt=\"Integrate email and social media marketing\" style=\"margin-left:250px;\"/>\r\n\r\n<i>image by Web Success Team at their website {Link to <a title=\"Integrate email and social media marketing\" href=\"http://websuccessteam.com/WSTblog/2012/03/email-marketing-relevant-age-social-networking/\" target=\"_blank\">http://websuccessteam.com/WSTblog/2012/03/email-marketing-relevant-age-social-networking/</a>}</i>\r\n\r\n<strong>Why to Integrate them?</strong>\r\nWe know social marketing is much effective and popular but studies have also showed that email marketing is still a major way of communicating with users personally. There are around 4+ billion email accounts, 1.5 million Facebook user accounts, twitter having 500 million accounts, LinkedIn 240+ million users where statistics show there are only 7 billion inhabitants on the earth. So that is actually an astonishing fact and number. So the facts of course point towards a future where everybody you know will be logged in to some kind of account almost every time or even more than one accounts at a time.\r\n\r\nS