sses</h3>\r\nThough it’s an old way of communicating business information but with advent of technology new ways have been introduced. Word of mouth is undoubtedly one of the most effective marketing strategy but negative points do exist here are some;\r\n1) Major weakness of WOM strategy is that it reaches targeted audience very slowly. Company needs to develop an effective plan and then executing that plan is another story. Social media platforms have made it simpler than ever before. Company just needs to write a blog post or status about referral program, offer bonus for the ones referring and posting it online.\r\n2) Limited audience can be acquired in much time. Company, its employees,\r\n3) Tracking who referred who is bit harder but again IT is resolving the issue in bets possible ways.\r\n4) What if customer sends forward negative remarks? This is a bitter reality attached with referral marketing.\r\n<h3>A winning example of referral campaign</h3>\r\nDrop-box used for storing data on cloud ran referral campaign in year 2009. In which they were providing free extra space to both the one referring and the one joining drop-box through referred link. The campaign set a fire and records shows more than 2.8 direct referrals were getting sent monthly.','An introduction to Referral marketing','','publish','open','open','','an-introduction-to-referral-marketing','','','2015-04-23 15:47:10','2015-04-23 19:47:10','',0,'http://adomattic.com/?p=300',0,'post','',0),(301,2,'2015-04-20 11:16:24','2015-04-20 15:16:24','Word “referral” means referring a person, product, service, place or any other thing to someone else for use or for taking any action. You must have heard your best friend talking about his favorite brand of shirts or favorite restaurant and its delicious food. This process involves referring things to others so they also know about it. Referrals are also widely used for marketing purpose to advertise and promote business, services and items and this process 