ublishers just publish them at their places. Their publishing points can be online forums, websites, facebook pages, or twitter followers circle.\r\nCustomer is simply the person, who sees ads on publishers place and makes an action of clicking link, submitting information on advertiser’s forum, making order or simply visiting the website. Arrival of customer and his actions on advertisers place completes the chain which is called conversion.\r\nAffiliate program commission payment models\r\nSellers and advertisers who sell out merchandise and services online or look for other affiliate business processes typically utilize one of the affiliate program charge payment models mentioned below:\r\nCost Per Sale (CPA)\r\nWhen a visitor referred to advertiser by the affiliated publisher clicks to purchase or complete a process of making order then advertiser must pay a specific amount to the publisher. A commission model dealing with this is called cost per acquisition or cost per sale.\r\n\r\nCost Per Lead (CPL)\r\nWhen a user or visitor redirected by affiliated publisher fill and submits a form on seller’s website then a model followed to deal payments is called Cost per Lead (CPL).\r\n\r\nCost Per Click (CPC)\r\nFor any click by user on the banner, link, ad, or image of merchant is considered for a payment model called cost per click. This click must redirect user to seller’s website.\r\n\r\nMechanism of affiliate marketing\r\nHow will it be figured out that the customer who visited website was referred by affiliate? Where did that customer belong to? Was that user actually sent to original seller? Which seller was the user redirected to as there are many affiliate sellers already? How many clicks or conversions were made in a specific time? You must be having all these questions in your mind. There are many techniques used by developers to overcome all affiliate marketing related aspects but the most common with lots of varieties is “using cookies”. Cookies are programming blocks that can save different types of data inside them. They can save conversion rates, name of seller’s website, how many clicks, when they were made, visitor’s data, their geographical location, browser information and a lot more. You might have saved your user name and password for any account, have you ever thought where they are saved. They are saved in cookie. But don’t worry cookies will not harm your privacy.','Affiliate marketing','','inherit','open','open','','298-revision-v1','','','2015-04-20 11:41:31','2015-04-20 15:41:31','',298,'http://adomattic.com/298-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(311,2,'2015-04-24 04:24:45','2015-04-24 08:24:45','The word “affiliate” simply means partnership. Affiliate marketing is the process of promoting others business on your forums or websites and then charging compensation for every click, visit, purchase customer makes. Affiliate marketing is the affiliation between three parties;\n\n1) Advertisers\n2) Publisher\n3) Customers\n<img src=\"http://www.jackmedia.com/skin/pages/images/affiliate_network/jackmedia_how-affiliate-marketing-works-infograph.jpg\" alt=\"Affiliate Marketing\" />\n<i><b>image by Jack Media at their website {link to <a href=\"http://www.ariscommunity.com/\" title=\"Arisd community\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.ariscommunity.com/</a>}  </b></i>\n\nIn affiliate marketing, <strong>advertiser</strong> can be anyone including an organization that wants to promote its products or services. The product and services can be of any type like computers, software, hardware, cars, clothes, online data security, cooking classes, and a lot more. The advertiser might be an individual who wants to sell out any course, E-book, home or any other thing. So basically all those who want to promote their products or services are advertisers.\n<strong>Publisher</strong> is someone who signs a contract with advertisers and promotes their business in exchange with money. Advertisers provide their banners, slides, images