rabbing their attention. Advertisers can send emails to new users to compel them for buying or can hit emails to previous users to persuade them for buying again. The field has emerged as one of the fastest growing online advertising trends in past few years. Reasons of its popularity are cheaper cost, less time consuming, reaching every customers personally. When advertising on landing pages you need to call and redirect your customers to your website but in E-mail marketing your customers will read your e-mails.\n<img src=\"http://jobcircle.pk/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Email-Marketing.jpg\" alt=\"Email marketing\" />\n<i>Image by Khurram Hussain at his website {link to }</i>\n&nbsp;\n<h4>Types of E-mail ads</h4>\nThere are 2 main types of E-mail ads which are following;\n<strong>   1) Direct e-mail ads</strong>\nThis category involves sending direct ad and promotional mails to a list of users. You might have your own email lists of viewers or the list of subscribers. You can also send direct mails to list of email addresses of prospects. You can also take assistance from service companies. They will give you option of sending e-mails to their email lists but you will have to pay for every email you send. They provide weekly and monthly packages too. Your email can have promotional messages, details and images of special offers or exciting new products and service information.\n<strong>   2) Transactional e-mails ads</strong>\nTransactional emails involve engaging users with specified actions and then send responses of those actions to their emails. For instance, if a user wants to reset its email account password so it will be asked to enter its email address. Once the person provides correct email send new password information to their emails. Other similar cases can be sending login verification, order details, order confirmation, account notification, any action they are supposed to take, or any other information based on user made actions.\nYou can also ask other companies or services to promote your business in their transactional messages. Latest software provide advanced features to create attractive emails, you can try them to catch eye of your user.\n<h4>How to make E-mail ads attractive?</h4>\nWe live in the era where user’s attention is money. Your user is not going to be someone technical every time. Most of the people focus more on beauty of content you have sent. Here are given some tips on how to write attractive email ads.\n1) Use interesting and colorful images that must be relevant.\n2) Use simple but as less text as possible. Study has showed people avoid reading bulk of words and get fascinated by visual content more.\n3) Provide links to your website, videos and services.\n4) Always use substituted wording with your image related to pictures. These images are sometimes not displayed so this text is then showed to user.\n5) Prefer testing your email before sending it to user. Check its impression and look by sending it to any of your other email accounts.\nNumber of software has been developed that you can use to create striking email ads. Keep one thing in view, your actions and mails must not be spam and should satisfy legal terms and conditions.','Advertise your business with E-mail marketing','','inherit','open','open','','304-autosave-v1','','','2015-04-24 03:46:55','2015-04-24 07:46:55','',304,'http://adomattic.com/304-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(331,2,'2015-04-21 11:14:21','2015-04-21 15:14:21','E-mail marketing as the name depicts, is advertising via mail. It involves sending E-mails to clients and grabbing their attention. Advertisers can send emails to new users to compel them for buying or can hit emails to previous users to persuade them for buying again. The field has emerged as one of the fastest growing online advertising trends in past few years. Reasons of its popularity are cheaper cost, less time consuming, reaching every customers personally. When advertising on landing pages yo