f decision makers.\n\nData is the heart of any company and it needs to be clear and organized. Company must know how data is related with other information, how everything is supposed to go on. For example, if company has hired 300 workers and is currently dealing with 1000 customers plus also keeping data of all products, services, and schedules. Then the company must have a strong database and a data warehouse. But to elaborate the inner structure a clear model must be made so stakeholders will have a clear notion of data.\n\nProcess involves close collaboration of expert data modelers with company stakeholders.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Types of data modeling</strong>\n\nMainly there are three data models in the way from requirement analysis to a complete functional database.\n<ul>\n	<li><strong>Conceptual data model</strong></li>\n</ul>\nAlso called semantic data model. The model deals with tool independent data model framed to show big picture of future information system and final data model. Model can have attributes with entities, some relationships and components of data but it will not cover deep details but just for conveying major thought. The model is then presented to owners of company; idea is made clear then if model is approved professionals sign an agreement for further work.\n<ul>\n	<li><strong>Logical data model</strong></li>\n</ul>\nOnce conceptual data model is approved, professional translate it into logical data model. This model draws a comprehensible structure of database. Keep in mind, one conceptual data model can have multiple logical data models. The LDM contains complete database structure that has all attributes, entities, all possible connections and relationships. Model is fully normalized but sometimes due to factors like change of time de-normalization can occur.\n<ul>\n	<li><strong>Physical data model</strong></li>\n</ul>\nFinal stage is the conversion of logical data mode into physical data model. Data is arranged into tables within 