iate business processes typically utilize one of the affiliate program charge payment models mentioned below:\r\n<strong>Cost Per Sale (CPA)</strong>\r\nWhen a visitor referred to advertiser by the affiliated publisher clicks to purchase or complete a process of making order then advertiser must pay a specific amount to the publisher. A commission model dealing with this is called cost per acquisition or cost per sale.\r\n\r\n<strong>Cost Per Lead (CPL)</strong>\r\nWhen a user or visitor redirected by affiliated publisher fill and submits a form on seller’s website then a model followed to deal payments is called Cost per Lead (CPL).\r\n\r\n<strong>Cost Per Click (CPC)</strong>\r\nFor any click by user on the banner, link, ad, or image of merchant is considered for a payment model called cost per click. This click must redirect user to seller’s website.\r\n<h3>Mechanism of Affiliate marketing</h3>\r\nHow will it be figured out that the customer who visited website was referred by affiliate? Where did that customer belong to? Was that user actually sent to original seller? Which seller was the user redirected to as there are many affiliate sellers already? How many clicks or conversions were made in a specific time? You must be having all these questions in your mind. There are many techniques used by developers to overcome all affiliate marketing related aspects but the most common with lots of varieties is “using cookies”. Cookies are programming blocks that can save different types of data inside them. They can save conversion rates, name of seller’s website, how many clicks, when they were made, visitor’s data, their geographical location, browser information and a lot more. You might have saved your user name and password for any account, have you ever thought where they are saved. They are saved in cookie. But don’t worry cookies will not harm your privacy.','Affiliate marketing','','inherit','open','open','','298-revision-v1','','','2015-04-24 04:25:12','2015-04-24 08:25:12','',298,'http://adomattic.com/298-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(410,2,'2015-04-24 05:49:04','2015-04-24 09:49:04','Google DoubleClick is a part of Google’s advertising campaign used by agencies, companies, publishers, marketers and other advertisers. Some famous clients of Google double click are Microsoft, Coca-cola, Motorola, Visa UA, Loreal and Apple Inc. it is said to be one of the initial application services provider serving banner ads especially for ads. In 1998 the company was linked with an internet report with AOL, Vista, Yahoo and Excite and was also ranked as one of the top 10 worldwide websites.\r\n\r\nGoogle DoubleClick is an ad based technology served mainly to advertising agencies and media organizations. Double click enables them to allow users visit, target, traffic and report on their interactive ad campaigns. Double Click Company’s major product line is called DART (Dynamic advertising reporting and targeting) especially designed for publishers and advertisers.\r\n\r\nDART technology is designed to automate the administration process of buying ads for advertisers called DFA (Double click for advertisers) and helps in managing ad inventory for publishers called DFP (double click for publishers). The purpose is to enhance buying procedure for advertisers and to reduce unsold inventory for publishers.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://www.google.com/help/hc/images/richmedia/chart.jpg\" alt=\"Google DoubleClick\" />\r\n\r\n<i>image by Google DoubleClick at their website {link to <a href=\"https://support.google.com/richmedia/answer/2453367?hl=en\" title=\"Google DoubleClick \" target=\"_blank\">https://support.google.com/richmedia/answer/2453367?hl=en</a>} </i>\r\n\r\nDouble click got <strong>Performics</strong> in 2004. Performics is a top performance marketing service provider that offers paid search, social display, natural search affiliate marketing, mobile advertising, search engine optimization and search engine marketing.  All these marketing performance services are taken in into DART system and rebrand DART search. Double click advertising exchange version 2007 have now even moved on by providing connection on advertising exchange in both media buyers and sellers, similarly as traditional stock exchange.\r\n<h2>Data collection via Google doubleClick</h2>\r\nTo collect user data Google DoubleClick targets many areas such as IP addresses, referrals to user information saved in cookies on their machines or business regulations set by any client. Here are some major kinds of collected information; operating system information, ISP (Internet service provider), Bandwidth data, Time of day and web browser. This data can also be used for the purpose to display customize ads to the visitors. Along with this, cookie information might be used to target ads depending on the number of times visitor has been exposed to any provided message, also called frequency capping.\r\n<h2>Cons and Pros of Google DoubleClick</h2>\r\n<strong>Cons</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Google takes its appropriate share from online advertising services from publishers and advertisers.</li>\r\n	<li>As Google possesses Gmail and has an unbelievable amount of data on its users, the whole misguided cookie/privacy dispute can reignite.</li>\r\n	<li>Microsoft and other companies failed the competition to buy DoubleClick which increases the possibility of developing strict tracking rules for cookies and can make information tracking harder.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Pros</strong>\r\n\r\nWhat are the possible merits now?\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Advertisers can collect relevant data about their visitors required for further tracking, reporting and analysis.</li>\r\n	<li>Any kid of display ad can be created and advertised such as online banners, paid search, natural search, E-mail ad or video and audio ad.</li>\r\n	<li>Allows cross platform tracking.</li>\r\n	<li>Image advertisements (banners can be run on Google\'s AdSense Network) could be merged to DART for Publishers</li>\r\n</ul>','How Google DoubleClick helps in marketing?','','inherit','open','open','','213-revision-v1','','','2015-04-24 05:49:04','2015-04-24 09:49:04','',213,'http://adomattic.com/213-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(411,2,'2015-04-24 05:51:57','2015-04-24 09:51:57','','download (2)','','inherit','open','open','','download-2','','','2015-04-24 05:51:57','2015-04-24 09:51:57','',213,'http://adomattic.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/download-2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(412,2,'2015-04-24 05:54:29','2015-04-24 09:54:29','&nbsp;\r\n\r\nMobile advertising that lies under mobile marketing is considered as one of the best ad practices. The reason is that it makes advertisers reach their customers on the go. Term “mobile ad” raises a thought in your mind that it might be a banner kind of ad or ads in search results. But the new advancements have made it go further than this. Mobile ads subsist in different number of formats now such as banners; short message service (SMS), short videos, vibration based sound ads and other responsive and interactive display ads. Both marketers and app publishers need to run their own ads to promote their apps and other products. Mobile advertising is suitable for every kind of business and app to be promoted.\r\n<h2>What to know before advertising on mobile?</h2>\r\nBefore you run ad on mobile you should consider the following points;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>What are the types of mobile ads that advertisers can make use of</li>\r\n	<li>What are different mobile devices that you will be running your ad on like smartphone, blackberry, iPhones and other devices that can make calls?</li>\r\n	<li>How can user click on the ad, what are the easiest and preferred ways?</li>\r\n	<li>Understand conversion rates.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Where mobile ads can appear and their types</h2>\r\n<table style=\"height: 554px; margin: 5px;\" border=\"2\" width=\"607\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"text-alig