ily budget and select how you will spend on advertising in Google AdWords. For instance you have set $2 CPC bid for your advertisement, then $2 is the maximum amount you will have to pay for one click on your advertisement.','What is Google AdWords and how it sparks marketing?','','inherit','open','open','','169-revision-v1','','','2015-04-24 06:32:05','2015-04-24 10:32:05','',169,'http://adomattic.com/169-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(425,2,'2015-04-24 06:37:18','2015-04-24 10:37:18','Digital attribution is the set of events based on user actions. These events or set of actions contribute in some manner to the desired digital marketing results. Each of these events is assigned values according to its importance in marketing and its impact on consumers. Digital attribution specifies what combination of events involves users in desired behavior, mostly referred to as conversions.\r\n\r\nThe current application of attribution marketing has emerged from transition of marketing from traditional to digital ways. The field is highly affected by large data collected through digital channels such as online questioners, social media platforms, conversion, Emails etc.\r\n\r\nIts main purpose is to quantify and study the effects each advertising impression leaves on purchase decision of user. Subsequent to analyzing and studying what influences customers more, marketers optimize media for conversions and compare the importance of different media channels for marketing, such as E-mail, affiliate marketing, social media networks, display ads and others.\r\n\r\nAnalyzing the whole conversion path across the whole marketing mix eliminates the accuracy challenge of analyzing data from isolated marketing means. Usually, attribution statistics are utilized by marketers to map future ad promotions and campaigns by evaluating which media assignments (ads) were the most cost-efficient as shown by metrics like eCPA (effective cost per action).\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://digitalmarketing-glossary.com/IMG/jpg/attribution-model5.jpg\" alt=\"digital attribution\" />\r\n\r\n<i>image by the digital marketing at their website {link to <a href=\"http://digitalmarketing-glossary.com/\" title=\"the digital marketing\" target=\"_blank\">http://digitalmarketing-glossary.com/</a>} </i>\r\n\r\n<strong>Models of attribution</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>            </strong>Rapid growth and popularity of digital advertisement and online marketing has concluded in large amount of user data for tracking, ROI and effectiveness of conversions. These new tendencies have affected the way marketers measure the effectiveness of marketing and advertising. The trends have also opened new door to development of new marketing metrics that are CPI (cost per impression), CPC (Cost per click), CPA (cost per acquisition/action), and click-through conversion. Besides this number of attribution modals have emerged with time since explosion of data and devices have boosted up the creation of attribution technology. Digital attribution is very important because it assists advertisers in analysing behaviors and responses of customers.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Single source attribution</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAlso known as single touch attribution, allocates all credit to single event or action for instance, last channel used to show ad, last click or initial click. Single attribution model does not justify and contribute to all elements involved in creating results. This is the reason model isn\'t considered verified and accurate especially by Google.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Fractional attribution</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThis attribution model comprise of consumer credit, U-curve models and equal weights. Here equal weight based models assign same amount of credit to all media channels and media mix, consumer credit involves studying guesswork or past experiences of customers to assign credits, and whole credit is allocated to first and final click in U-curve where idle actions are ignored across conversion path.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Algorithmic attribution</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThis model of attribution utilizes proprietary algorithms to allocate conversion among all touch points before conversions with the help of auto scripts to locate where credit is unpaid. Model is started from very first event level and assesses converting and non-converting paths crosswise all media channels. After that weights are combined to figure out hidden associations and correlations inside marketing.','Digital attribution','','inherit','open','open','','228-revision-v1','','','2015-04-24 06:37:18','2015-04-24 10:37:18','',228,'http://adomattic.com/228-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(426,2,'2015-04-24 06:39:14','2015-04-24 10:39:14','What are unique digital marketing challenges when using digital media as a tool for marketing and advertising? There would be several touch points as far as digital is concerned with digital marketing challenges. A recent study by <strong>SalesForce Marketing Cloud </strong>has shown around 84% of global marketers is planning to switch and spend on digital marketing in year 2015. 42% are B2C marketers and 38% are B2B marketers in the survey. Of course there are number of digital advertising channels but most of marketers are planning to spend more on the following top areas;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>More than 70% marketers are thinking to spend social media advertising and marketing.</li>\r\n	<li>Around 67% people are planning to spend on social media engagement.</li>\r\n	<li>67% marketers voted for mobile apps that track customer’s.</li>\r\n	<li>66% marketers preferred using mobile apps to reach their customers.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThe report showed they are having new digital marketing challenges. Marketers stated that they are trying to create more by spending less and trying to grab their consumers. There are now more means of targeting specific users based on languages, areas, ages, and timing than ever before. All alo