nd customer circle there. You can post short videos introducing your business. You can also write about what is special about your company. Face-book is the largest social network application out there right now and it’s essential for you to have be present there to grow your business and of course to connect with your customers and followers. Large number of business based face-book groups and pages already exist, you can advertise yourself their so more people will see you.\r\n\r\nThird is Twitter, a great way to connect with other professionals, businessmen and also get a lot of information. It is also an efficient way to get lots of news and learn about new business strategies as well.\r\n\r\nFourth one is LinkedIn. It is a resume kind of website. Your LinkedIn profile holds information about your previous experiences, your current ongoing job or business and you can also publish your qualification data. On LinkedIn you should build connections with professionals, your consumers, vendors, sellers, former employees and your friends. LinkedIn profile must be robust and make yourself standout. Do not forget asking for recommendations, people love to see testimonials.\r\n\r\nLast but not least, have a blog. Some people don’t like to write but there are ways to get around that you can long blogs, short advertisements. You can also create video blog so if you are comfortable on camera then put a short video clip on your blog in place of writing out text post. Having blog establishes you as an expert. The more contacts you have online, the easier it will be for people to find you online, they will like to know and trust you and will love to do business with you.\r\n\r\n<img class=\" alignleft\" src=\"http://activex.com.pk/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/social-media-marketing.jpg\" alt=\"Social Media Networks\" width=\"334\" height=\"278\" />\r\n\r\n<i>image by infinitemarketing at their website {link to <a href=\"http://infinitemarketing.info/social-media-marketing/\" title=\"infinitemarketing\" target=\"_blank\">http://infinitemarketing.info/social-media-marketing/</a>} </i>\r\n\r\nOther online means to advertise your business are Youtube,Instagram, Google+, Yelp and many others. All these ways are low cost with high results. So if you need to start with online marketing then get a website, make accounts on face-book, twitter, LinkedIn, yahoo, Youtube and start a blog and you will be on your way to marketing success.','Social Media Impact On Marketing','','inherit','open','open','','125-revision-v1','','','2015-04-24 06:55:22','2015-04-24 10:55:22','',125,'http://adomattic.com/125-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(434,2,'2015-04-24 06:59:44','2015-04-24 10:59:44','Native advertisement can be a full page advertisement between pages of articles or it might be a tweet on twitter, it can be a status with images or other media on facebook or a post on advertisement forums. Native advertisements take on the similar format as of the webpage they are displayed on. It is mainly about how advertisements work with online publications to reach audience. It is the simplest form of display advertisement and contextual advertisements. Major difference between native and other form of display advertisement is that, other forms are highlighted using pop-ups or side sections on webpage while native advertisement comes in the flow of content.\n\nThe publications usually incorporating native ads enhance their quality by providing relevant information about different products in their articles and blogs. According to the study of IPG media lab there is similar percentage of sharing and reading native advertisement as there is of reading and sharing content. This is also considered one of the core reasons of its popularity.\n\nThe content published on authentic and famous websites go viral. The reason of incorporating advertisements is not just to share the content but also to cut the extra costs for advertisers which come when other formats on display advertising is used.\n\n<img src=\"https://tctechcrunch2011.files.wordpress.com/2012/06/native-ad-framework-1.jpg\" alt=\"native marketing\" />\n\n<strong>Platforms supporting native advertisement</strong>\n\nThere are two main types of platforms that support native advertising, open, closed and hybrid platforms.\n\n<strong>Closed platforms</strong>\n\n<strong>                        </strong>These platforms create profiles and contents and then promote the content having native advertisement according to specified confines. The instances are twitter promoted tweets, shared posts on facebook or content published on different websites.\n\n<strong>Open platforms</strong>\n\nContrasting closed platforms, open platforms promote content across number of other platform and native ads go to external platforms.\n\nMany mobile platforms have also been developed and launched for same purpose.\n\n<strong>Different Examples of native ads</strong>\n\nFew examples of native ads are listed below;\n<ul>\n	<li>Native advertisements can appear in editorial contents and online editorials.</li>\n	<li>They can be included in videos.</li>\n	<li>It can be in the form of sponsored content for which brand pays to publisher.</li>\n	<li>Native advertisements can be a branded content created by brand for the publisher.</li>\n	<li>They can be incorporated in your social media posts, shared videos and images.</li>\n	<li>They might be in the form of In-feed ads pushing user to other publishing websites.</li>\n	<li>They also displayed as search results on different search engines such as google, yahoo and Bing.</li>\n</ul>\nNative ads must be in the similar flow as content.\n\n<strong>Advantages</strong>\n\nChief benefits provided by native ads are;\n<ul>\n	<li>Great possibility of customer’s visit to the content and surety of user’s response.</li>\n	<li>Consumers consider them content and view them for same number of seconds.</li>\n	<li>Effective to obtain branding goals.</li>\n	<li>The increase purchase rate 18% higher than banner ads.</li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n\nThe native content that is about viewer, reader and listener is one considered best. Native ads are supposed to enhance the quality of content by providing relevant ads to guide the reader.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nPhoto Credit : https://www.flickr.com/photos/r00s/','What Is Native Advertisement?','','inherit','open','open','','90-autosave-v1','','','2015-04-24 06:59:44','2015-04-24 10:59:44','',90,'http://adomattic.com/90-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(435,2,'2015-04-24 07:00:29','2015-04-24 11:00:29','Native advertisement can be a full page advertisement between pages of articles or it might be a tweet on twitter, it can be a status with images or other media on facebook or a post on advertisement forums. Native advertisements take on the similar format as of the webpage they are displayed on. It is mainly about how advertisements work with online publications to reach audience. It is the simplest form of display advertisement and contextual advertisements. Major difference between native and other form of display advertisement is that, other forms are highlighted using pop-ups or side sections on webpage while native advertisement comes in the flow of content.\r\n\r\nThe publications usually incorporating native ads enhance their quality by providing relevant information about different products in their articles and blogs. According to the study of IPG media lab there is similar percentage of sharing and reading native advertisement as there is of reading and sharing content. This is also considered one of the core reasons of its popularity.\r\n\r\nThe content published on authentic and famous websites go viral. The reason of incorporating advertisements is not just to share the content but also to cut the extra costs for advertisers which come when other formats on display advertising is used.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://tctechcrunch2011.files.wordpress.com/2012/06/native-ad-framework-1.jpg\" alt=\"native mar