e technologies like advertising exchanges and real time bidding that is creating new ways of purchasing and selling advertisements have dragged data science in the top of the “Industry must have” skills.\nIn present era customers have all means of approaching your advertisements online from anywhere and anytime. These sources provide easy ways to the advertisers for collecting and saving required data of consumers that can provide them competitive advantages. Here comes the notion of “Big Data” to easily target and communicate with today’s busy consumer. Points mentioned below can be used by advertisers to use data in best possible ways.\n1) Comprehend available data sources and decide when and how to utilize them.\n2) The consumers are creating mountains of data by the time they have switched to internet. As a conclusion advertisers are daily getting huge amount of data in the form of images, text, emails, social media posts and interaction. All such data is huge and un-structured. The very first step to make the data useful for future operations is to organize the data using Big Data platform. Unstructured data is a problem but its organized form is the solution.\n3) Use data to take deep insights and to make best decisions ever. Apply real-time analysis and apply strategies to detect events in real time. Such as consumers buying online or any fraudulent transaction taking place.\n4) Deliver relevant, personalized and targeted ads. Focus a group or segment and advertise relevant data to your services or products.\n5) Delivering relevant data alone is not enough but communicating it to the exact consumer holds the similar level of importance. Latest technologies have now provided with facilities to trace consumer’s location and send advertisements to them.\n\nData-driven advertising is clearly exploding in current era. Big data applications and analytics technologies are enhancing and soon will make marketers and advertisers to take out more from consumer’s data.\n