ditional and modern mobile ads and a short overview of responsive types of mobile advertisements. In this article we will have a bit deeper view of responsive and interactive formats of mobile ads. \r\n	As we discussed previously that with growing e-marketing latest ad trends are also emerging with secure interaction. In past few years’ great interest for m-commerce have been studied.  Now the biggest issue is how to involve users without annoying them and by increasing their interests. Because users never like to be interrupted by popping up ads while playing games, using any other app or internet surfing. So to engage users more ad maker platforms and technologists are introducing such ways that will surely be less annoying and surety of user interaction. \r\nMobile ads formats \r\n	You will come through large number of mobile ads campaign and attractive display formats used if you ever make a research. Here we are elaborating major mobile ad formats so you can understand where and how they are produced and their effects on conversion rates.\r\n1)	Mobile text ads\r\nMobile text ads are similar to those on desktops the only difference comes on number of text ads displayed per page. In desktop more textual ads can be displayed than on mobile browsers. There are number of facilities and platforms available such as Bing, Yahoo, Google AdWords, Facebook ads (that can be displayed on both desktops and mobiles), twitter, and Google Adsense. \r\n	Mobile ad platforms also offer auto fine-tune facilities to fit your ad in some circumstances automatically so you will get more user responses. One example for this can be the placement of most relevant enabled extensions in place of second line of Ad description in Google AdWords. If you want to make text Ad then make sure it should not exceed 3 lines. Content should be relevant, simple and friendly.     \r\n2)	Image ads\r\nThere are two major types of mobile ads\r\n1)	Interstitial mobile \r\nThese are full screen image ads with higher CPC and click-through rate. It is considered better than banner ads. Its standard image size for phones is 300 x 250 and 1024 x 768 for tablets.   \r\n2)	Banner image ads\r\n\r\nThe most commonly used image ads displayed on the top of screen. it also appear on the top while using app. Image sizes for banners ads can be 640X100, which is the standard one. \r\n3)	App promotion advertisements\r\nThey come in the form of “click to download”, one of the most engaging and effective way for users to communicate hence also called app install ads. These ads are mostly utilized by app developers to promote their apps and are automatically displayed on positions where they will have the strongest impact. Some of the famous app promotion ad campaigns comprise mobile app installs, ads in mobile apps, and mobile app engagement. Ad can hold a section having app name, app icon, bit description, rating stars, price, and download option and screen shots. \r\n4)	Call-only ads\r\nCall only ads are only workable for devices that can make calls. They redirect customers to the point where the make call to advertisers and marketers. The ad can have business name, description, phone number, and URL of your website. \r\n5)	WAP-mobile ads\r\nAds are mainly used to advertise your mobile friendly website. The ad will have 2 lines of short description and third line having website URL. Users will just need to click on link to reach your website. ','Interactive formats of mobile ads','','inherit','open','open','','302-revision-v1','','','2015-04-24 10:54:07','2015-04-24 14:54:07','',302,'http://adomattic.com/302-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(447,2,'2015-04-24 11:01:02','2015-04-24 15:01:02','In our previous article “Types and trends of Mobil advertising” we discussed about mobile advertising, comparison between traditional and modern mobile ads and a short overview of responsive types of mobile advertisements. In this article we will have a bit deeper view of responsive and interacti