igms. Now we use relational database and relational access paradigms. Data can be saved and access from multiple machines. After sometime search engines emerged. These engines deployed different algorithm to control, save and structure huge amount of data to give better search results. Daily data of thousands of people is getting saved in to databases. In this context AI is needed to give logical infrastructure to big data and to control their sources.\r\n\r\nAI is heavily used in machine learning, where data and algorithms together are used to predict out the results. Mostly AI based machines and computer programs are designed in an experience learning way. They learn from previous experiences or inserted examples.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>Few AI based examples in big data</h3>\r\nGoogle saves user’s click and acquisition to provide better search results to next users. The more any web page is accessed the more its rank and probability of getting showed in search results will be higher. Similarly utilizing AI based techniques Facebook improves its visibility and availability of data. Facebook mostly shows posts and pictures from those pages which are visited more by user. All these things are to make user experience better and to get loyal buyers.\r\n\r\nAI techniques figure out user interest patterns, and also analyze its behavior to perform task better next time.\r\n\r\n<img class=\" aligncenter\" src=\"https://www.inovancetech.com/img/blog/diagram1.png\" alt=\"Artificial intelligence supports Big data\" />\r\n\r\n<i>image by inovancetech at their website {link to <a title=\"inovancetech\" href=\"https://www.inovancetech.com/buzzwords.html\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.inovancetech.com/buzzwords.html</a>} </i>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>Role of AI and big data in marketing</h3>\r\n<strong>            </strong>\r\n\r\nBig data is mainly relevant to consumers, advertising and marketing. Company needs to have much data about its customers to get a big circle and to provide what is actually according to their interest. Companies mostly send messages to their consumers or reach them on social media platforms. When being visited by user the company must be able to know what their customers need. For this they must have enough information about them.  The company needs to apply data modeling techniques if they want to know customer’s search patterns. These modeling, data analyzing, and reporting techniques can be controlled by AI to improve user experience and to assist businesses in collecting and managing user data.','How Artificial intelligence supports Big data','','publish','open','open','','how-artificial-intelligence-supports-big-data','','','2015-04-28 18:00:26','2015-04-28 22:00:26','',0,'http://adomattic.com/?p=466',0,'post','',0),(467,2,'2015-04-28 17:56:29','2015-04-28 21:56:29','Currently social media platforms, mobile devices, sensors and other sources are providing ways to collect huge data called “Big Data”. These data sources and data needs to be managed accordingly to for best possible use. Artificial Intelligence is one of the largest growing fields of science. AI is having different applications in multiple fields that are robotics, bioinformatics, finance, heavy industry, music, games, transportation, computer science and big data too. AI has been utilized in a number of different ways to assist capturing and structuring big data and AI is used to evaluate big data for major insights. In this article we will discuss how AI boosts uses and management of big data sources and what role is data playing in AI.\r\n\r\n<strong>AI uses and its role in big data</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>            </strong>In old days data was mostly saved on single computer and only few people could access them. There were fewer ways of collecting data so they didn’t have to worry about it much. But as technology has grown great difference has occurred in data collection methods and data access paradigms. Now we use relational database and relatio