ice. To catch more customers they started their referral program. The referral program gives people and their referred people additional free storage space. This is a well-known referral program: Dropbox’s refer-a-friend program enduringly augmented signups by 60%, with users sending 2.8 million direct referral invites by month of April 2010. In the month of September 2008 the Dropbox was having 100,000 registered accounts. While in 2010 they had around 4,000,000 users. According to their studies 35% of accounts were through their referral method.\r\n\r\nThe referral program of Dropbox was much effective because it rewards additional storage space, something that was much interest to usage and pleasure of their service.\r\n<img src=\"http://www.referralsaasquatch.com/assets/best-customer-referral-program-example-4.png\" alt=\"Referral program of Dropbox\" />\r\n<i>image by Referral SaaSquatch at their website {link to <a title=\"Referral SaaSquatchhttp://www.referralsaasquatch.com/best-saas-customer-referral-program-example/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.referralsaasquatch.com/best-saas-customer-referral-program-example/</a>} </i>\r\n<h3><strong> </strong><strong>Referral program by PayPal</strong></h3>\r\nPayPal ran referral program according who which they paid the consumers who reffered them to any of their other friend. The referral program boosted their user growth up to 7% to 10%. And soon customers were boosted to 100 million clients.\r\n\r\nDavid Sacks, the original CEO of PayPal, stated “that PayPal literally had to pay to those who referred it to their friends”. The referral program gave up far better ROI (return of investment) than triditional marketing plans. The company only continued the refer-to-friend program until they reached their target level of users. But the program was available to merchant but soon after reaching target audience that was also dropped.\r\n<img src=\"http://blog.referralcandy.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/referral-paypal-580x