utationally to figure out user’s interest patterns, their behaviors and easiest ways of interaction.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #000000;\">Hence topic of big data is very broad and new technologies and trends are getting introduced on daily basis. In this article we are providing idea of some of the latest and best technology. These technologies are helping people to cope with big adat problems effectively</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong> </strong></span>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Column-oriented databases</strong></span></h3>\r\n<span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>            </strong>old, row based databases were considered best for online transaction processing. They provided high update speeds but failed in query performance. This failure was due to high volume of data and their unstructured nature.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #000000;\">Then were introduced column-oriented databases considered one of the best Big Data Technologies. These databases focused more on columns rather than rows. It provided big data compression  and fastest query times. Their only demerit is they support batch updates onlyand slower update times in comparison to traditional databases.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #000000;\"> </span>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Schema-less databases, or NoSQL databases</strong></span></h3>\r\n<span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>            </strong>number of databases fall in this category, for instance document stores and key-value stores. They mainly focus on storing and retrieving large amount of structured and unstructured data. they have covered almost all of the traditional databases issues and restrictions such as read-write inconsistencies.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #000000;\"> </span>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>MapReduce</strong></span></h3>\r\n<span style=\"color: #000000;\">MapReduce is a programming based model. It is used for enormous data processing and execution scalability next to several thousands of servers and clusters of servers.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #000000;\">To practically implement MapReduce two things must be given;</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">First part is “Map” task. In Map task a dataset given as input is transformed into set of pairs of keys and values, also called tuples.</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Second task is called “Reduced”. In reduced task output tuples of “Map” are joined together to build a reduced set of tuples or pairs of keys/values.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong> </strong></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #000000;\"> </span>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>WibiData</strong></span></h3>\r\n<span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>            </strong>WibiData is an effective bog data technology that is a combined effort of web analytics with Hadoop. It’s developed on the top of Hbase which is a database layer built over Hadoop. Using WibiData users can collect user information and can analyse them in more effective manner. It also enables  real-time responses to users interests and behaviors for instance, displaying data according to previous search patters, showing personalized content and decisions.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #000000;\"> </span>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>PLATFORA</strong></span></h3>\r\n<span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>            </strong>Hadoop is a low level implemenmtation of MapReduce that is its major weakness and drawback. This makes it require to be operated by professionals only. Their techniques such as testing, processing and preparing take large amount of time. Which doesn’t allow users to enjoy their experiences. But PLATFORA platform converts user’s queries into Hadoop queries and tasks. That’s the technique it uses to create abstraction layer that can be used by anyone to simplify and structure datasets saved in Hadoop.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #000000;\"> </span>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Big Data in the cloud</strong></span></h3>\r\n<span style=\"color: #000000;\">Research and studies have shown that a large number of big data techniques are linked with cloud. Already hosted Hadoop clusters are being sold by large number of vendors. These Hadoop clusters are designed according to user’s requirements. Previous techniques mentioned in the articles either have cloud versions built into them or are completely cloud based. Cloud computing have enabled companies to have more value of their large data than ever before.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img src=\"http://images.techhive.com/images/article/2014/09/big_data_analytics_thinkstock_470971869-100439197-primary.idge.jpg\" alt=\"Latest Big Data Technologies\" /></span>\r\n\r\n<i><span style=\"color: #000000;\">image by ComputerWorld their website {link to <a style=\"color: #000000;\" title=\" \" href=\"http://www.computerworld.com/article/2690856/8-big-trends-in-big-data-analytics.html\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.computerworld.com/article/2690856/8-big-trends-in-big-data-analytics.html</a>}</span> </i>','Latest Big Data Technologies','','publish','open','open','','latest-big-data-technologies','','','2015-05-11 16:42:54','2015-05-11 20:42:54','',0,'http://adomattic.com/?p=611',0,'post','',0),(612,2,'2015-05-11 16:34:19','2015-05-11 20:34:19','Big data is a term used to show large data collected via different means, but mostly to refer user data collected through conversions, online platforms, mobile phones and other such sources. This data is evaluated computationally to figure out user’s interest patterns, their behaviors and easiest ways of interaction.\r\n\r\nHence topic of big data is very broad and new technologies and trends are getting introduced on daily basis. In this article we are providing idea of some of the latest and bes