xpected to interpret the data into meaningful information to find effective business insights.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #000000;\">Third challenge is of accessing and connecting data. Research shows most of the data points are not linked yet. Lake of connectivity and access prevent companies from having right platforms to collect and supervise the information in their organization.  Accenture and Siemens formed a venture collaborative in the smart grid field. Reason is to provide services and solutions for data collection, system connectivity and data management. These collaborative offerings will enable organizations to connect operational technologies with their data. one of its examples is real-time grid management, with other information technologies.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #000000;\">Rapidly changing information technology is counted as fourth major problem. Data management and analysis technologies are changing on daily basis. So companies require easiest and best ways to cope up with fastest growing technology. User data collection and analytics require advance technology manager that can always build and suggest correct IT architecture. The system must be adaptable to new changes efficiently.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #000000;\"> </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #000000;\">Fifth challenge is managing finance strategies, IT functions, engineering tasks, procurement, authorization, validity and access to data within the organization. Managing ownerships is also included. These organizational issues must be resolved effectively to come-up with innovative ways of performing business functions.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #000000;\">Last but not least, data security issues are major threat. Effective IT architacures must be designed to avoid any uncertainty.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Major Challenges in Big Data','','publish','open','open','','major-challenges-in-big-data','','','2015-05-15 10:58:32','2015-05-15 14:58:32','',0,'http://adomattic.com/?p=623',0,'post','',0),(624,2,'2015-05-14 16:53:24','2015-05-14 20:53:24','Almost every second industry is using data to create and add some value to its business now. Companies came through new amazing techniques of data analysis, data management and data collection with the advent of internet, mobile phones and other similar technologies. These technologies also helped in increasing communication with customer dynamically. All these things together brought number of opportunities for companies. In number of popular organizations these technologies are affecting the way services are managed and delivered. That ranges from reactive approach to predictive and preventive approach.\r\n\r\n<strong>Major challenges</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>            </strong>When we talk about big data then we must think of something very big that must be managed and utilized effectively. Similar is the case for big data. there are several challenges that big data brings with itself. The biggest challenge is how business is going to extract value out of collected data.\r\n\r\nAs I mentioned before the first issue for companies is how to collect only required data. as different kind of data can come to any company but how to sort out which should be kept and used in future. It also holds problem of how to use this data in best possible way. Of course company will use it for some valuable purpose. But there must be some affordable techniques to polish the data. for many companies, creating data-based business means doing something innovative. They think out of the box, search for revenue models and try to avoid traditional business models.\r\n\r\nSecond major challenge for companies is to get right people and tools for working with data. Companies are trying their best to seek-out young people who are not just passionate but also have good skills of working with technologies. These people are also expected to interpret the data into meaningful information to find effective business insights.\r\n\r\nThird challenge is of accessing and connecting data. Research shows most of the data points are not linked yet. Lake of connectivity and access prevent companies from having right platforms to collect and supervise the information in their organization.  Accenture and Siemens formed a venture collaborative in the smart grid field. Reason is to provide services and solutions for data collection, system connectivity and data management. These collaborative offerings will enable organizations to connect operational technologies with their data. one of its examples is real-time grid management, with other information technologies.\r\n\r\nRapidly changing information technology is counted as fourth major problem. Data management and analysis technologies are changing on daily basis. So companies require easiest and best ways to cope up with fastest growing technology. User data collection and analytics require advance technology manager that can always build and suggest correct IT architecture. The system must be adaptable to new changes efficiently.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFifth, leveraging big data often means working across functions like IT, engineering, finance and procurement and the ownership of data is fragmented across the organization. To address these organizational challenges means finding new ways of collaborating across functions and businesses.\r\n\r\nFinally, security concerns about data protection are a major obstacle preventing companies from taking full advantage of their data.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Major Challenges in Big Data','','inherit','open','open','','623-revision-v1','','','2015-05-14 16:53:24','2015-05-14 20:53:24','',623,'http://adomattic.com/623-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(625,2,'2015-05-14 16:54:08','2015-05-14 20:54:08','Almost every second industry is using data to create and add some value to its business now. Companies came through new amazing techniques of data analysis, data management and data collect