 conversion tracking systems. Technical faults can be major reasons of loosing affiliates. It also results in lost revenues and lost customers.\r\nThe technology must be set appropriately so marketer will be able to track affiliates better to reward and reimburse them. It’s better for marketers to have an online store linked with affiliate program. While they can also explore third party options available via different affiliate programs.\r\n<h3>2) Set best affordable prices</h3>\r\nIn affiliate agreements a marketer is supposed to pay every time sale or any decided transaction is generated from affiliate’s side. Affiliates can use a simple link with one or two lines of description to drive traffic to website. It can be comprehensive articles with videos and images to describe all features and aspects of product.\r\nInfluential affiliates can have large following on Facebook, websites, Twitter, YouTube, Instegram and blog. Their popularity surely results in large contracts from marketers. They might have several products in-line to represent.\r\nExperts prefer following affiliate marketing for products lying between $60 and $100. Significant number of sales can be made with these price points and appropriate commissions. Products lying below this range might provide less affiliate revenue while products above might not be sold readily.\r\n<h3>3) Work with right affiliates</h3>\r\nAffiliates give their best to gain popularity. Their popularity and following circle somehow bounds them and makes them choosy about affiliate agreements. They never agree on working with less reliable companies.\r\nSimilarly affiliates prefer advertising product relevant to their field. Affiliates have their own niches so entrepreneurs should only target and make affiliations with those who fall in their circle. For instance, if as a marketer you run a business of kitchen utensils then your targeted affiliates must be restaurant owners, foodies and other related to this field. They can advertise your product by relating it to some of their best services. But surely marketers must be ready to spend enough to get noticeable results.\r\n<h3>4) Make it clear and straightforward</h3>\r\nFederal Trade Commission has set rules for affiliate programs. According to them disclosures between both parties must be clear and straight forward. Marketers must carefully monitor what their affiliates are publishing about their products. Information must be authentic and provided with proofs.\r\n<h3>5) Try to design banners and advertising content yourself</h3>\r\nIt’s better to prepare advertising content yourself and then sending to affiliates for publishing. This way you can avoid every kind of misunderstanding.\r\n<h3>6) Keep yourself up-to-date</h3>\r\nKeep checking what your affiliates are posting or whether they are posting it according to the agreement or not.','How affiliate marketing can help Entrepreneurs','','publish','open','open','','affiliate-marketing-can-help-entrepreneurs','','','2015-05-16 16:39:55','2015-05-16 20:39:55','',0,'http://adomattic.com/?p=649',0,'post','',0),(650,2,'2015-05-16 16:22:36','2015-05-16 20:22:36','We have already discussed Affiliate Marketing in one of our previous articles. It simply is kind of business in which two marketers or companies or people make affiliation. Affiliate advertises marketer’s products on its firm, page, account or website and gets paid for each transaction. Many of today’s famous social media personalities have taken affiliate marketing as one of their earning methods. They might have a successful blog, a social media account with large following or any Facebook page and group with millions of members. Entering into affiliate marketing terms will give benefit of reaching large audience to entrepreneur and people’s trust into affiliates will be a major plus. Methods of promotion include testimonials, banners, links, videos, images and other similar ways.\r\nThe payment is mostly not made in advance but pa