 that your stuff is genuine. The owner can either upload any short audio or video of introducing his business to people. Voice and gestures should be kept original. While providing details there must be no exaggeration of products. Keep in mind, readers and visitors always want to know the author behind the blog.\r\n<h3>2) Be Original to win trust</h3>\r\nKeep information authentic and real. Try to provide proves of everything you show to your audience. Online frauds are so common and several cases have been reported that now people think several times before trusting any online site. So to earn their trust verification and authentication are must.\r\n<h3>3) Two-way communication is preferred</h3>\r\nTwo communications not only help you getting responses from your audience but also make you measure the health of your site. Putting option of readers comment is one of the best ways for engaging your customers. For the new visitors these comments will be endorsement and will show activeness of the website. Being an owner one should reply to user’s comments positively or should hire someone to give regular responses to users.\r\n<h3>4) Third party verification</h3>\r\nCompany can share social proofs, verification license from any third party or testimonials to prove its services verified to its users. Company can make affiliations with other more popular companies to advertise its services to large audience.\r\n<h3>5) Stay Honest</h3>\r\nHonesty is the best policy. Always let your users know what your site is doing and why is it important. Honesty is the only thing that will make your site live longer and will help you win more traffic. Inform your audience about your affiliates and the links you share with them. Acknowledge your mistakes and improve them.\r\n<h3>6) Be on the scene</h3>\r\nFollow the right track and always stay visible to your audience. To stay in front of their eyes all the time company can use social networking platforms. These users cannot only be th