s can easily be customized to display options like “Get it now”, “Speak to our experts now”, “Don’t miss and call now” etc. the feature can display both a phone number as well as call button.\r\n<h3>How to view Call-Only conversion?</h3>\r\nIn December 2014, a Custom columns option in AdWords was released by Google. The feature facilitates advertisers utilizing call tracking numbers to have a custom column for mobile calls inside the Google AdWords reporting interface.\r\nFor the customers who are already tracking calls as conversions setting up custom column will be very easy. Here are the steps for setting custom column.\r\nStep 1) Select custom column option and click on column tab.\r\nStep 2) now you can create a new column with calls segment, name and appropriate description.\r\nStep 3) Check all AdWord data and all website call conversions.\r\n\r\nAdvantage of this added feature is that it gives advertisers of what is the total conversion rate its Google AdWord is getting. Plus how many of all those conversions are call-only conversions. Advertiser can put up custom columns down to the keyword level to track which AdWord campaigns, keywords and ad groups are receiving more calls and conversions from customers. This amazing feature gives more ease in AdWord to different agencies, companies, and advertisers. The feature also shows popularity of only-call AdWord option to show how effective it is for increasing conversions.\r\n<h3>Benefits of Call-Only campaign</h3>\r\n• People now want everything on their fingertips and that is something exactly provided by this campaign.\r\n• Easy and quick communication.\r\n• You can share business number with large audience either within an ad group or with whole campaign.\r\n• Direct calls to your business.\r\n• Show level of activeness your business has among your users.\r\n• Option can be optimized to be displayed only when business can take calls else it will be disable.\r\n• You can increase your clickthrough rate with call conversions.\r\n<img src=\"http://searchitlocal.co.uk/images/storyimg/thumb_d1425031096.jpg\" alt=\"Call-Only\" />\r\n\r\nImage at <a href=\"http://searchitlocal.co.uk/news.php?id=108\">http://searchitlocal.co.uk/news.php?id=108</a>','Mobile Call-Only Campaigns by Google AdWords','','publish','open','open','','mobile-call-only-campaigns-by-google-adwords','','','2015-05-19 15:58:15','2015-05-19 19:58:15','',0,'http://adomattic.com/?p=678',0,'post','',0),(679,2,'2015-05-19 15:50:55','2015-05-19 19:50:55','Call-only campaign is another exciting and effective feature from Google AdWords. This feature displays phone number, business information and call button to users. As the feature is making call option hence optimized to display on mobile phones. CTA or call-to-action holds phone number of advertiser that prompts user to make a call whenever user searches for business information. The person doesn’t reach website of owner by clicking on call-to-action option but makes a call.\r\nA study by Google shows, around 70% mobile phone users prefer using call option for making direct call to business rather than going for detailed information. This study proves the success of this feature and that it holds power to reach large audience effectively.\r\nThe feature has quickly won immense position among other conversion methods. For each click now the page will not be redirected to any site but a phone call to owner will be made. And website will be paid for each click.\r\nThe feature becomes more valuable when advertisers only prefer calls as leads. Most of the customers now are on phones and prefer having things on their finger tips. Now they are increasingly doing searches on mobile phones and want to be able to communicate directly with businesses.\r\nCall-only buttons can easily be customized to display options like “Get it now”, “Speak to our experts now”, “Don’t miss and call now” etc. the feature can display both a phone number as well as call button.\r\n<h3>\r\nHo