xtual content exactly conveys your message but pictorial content can mislead users due to lack of clarity. To make best pictorial (video and image) content an advertiser should keep following tips in kind.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://blog.zopim.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/video-marketing.jpg\" alt=\"video and image content\" />\r\n\r\nImage at <a href=\"https://blog.zopim.com/2014/12/03/nine-benefits-video-marketing/\">https://blog.zopim.com/2014/12/03/nine-benefits-video-marketing/</a>\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n<h3> Importance of Production value in video and image content</h3>\r\nTaking care of production value is very important. Company must concentrate on the quality of lightening, scenery, sounds, props, graphics, audio, camera angles, effects and other stuff effecting video and image content. Marketers shouldn’t hesitate investing into production value even if they don’t have professionals.\r\n<h3>Know your Audience</h3>\r\nIn many of our previous articles we have already mentioned the importance of knowing your audience. As a marketer all your terms, conditions, policies and deals must be clear to your targeted audience. In marketing and every type of communication the first rule is that you should know who your targeted audience are and what kind of content they would prefer. Increase their awareness with a stuff that should contain a simple and easy to understand content. Try decreasing the level of confusion as much as possible in your content.\r\n<h3><strong>Keep it simple and short</strong></h3>\r\nNobody likes long videos and complicated images that are hard to understand.  Try keeping stuff short, simple and sweet.\r\n<h3>Professionals are always better</h3>\r\nTaking help from professionals and video/image making experts is preferable than trying it yourself. Being a marketer your focus should be more towards big picture rather than controlling small production issues. No doubt hiring experts cost enough money. But it saves your time, effort and provi